@startuml

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
}

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
    DiamondBorderColor #856404
    StartColor #212529
    EndColor #212529
    BarColor #495057
}

skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    TitleFontColor #212529
    TitleFontSize 13
}

title Parallel SMT Batch Processing

|ParallelSmtBatchProcessor|
start

:Receive **processRecords**(List<SourceRecord> records);
note right
  Called by the embedded engine
  with a full batch of raw
  SourceRecords to process
end note

:Log DEBUG — submitting **N** records\nfor parallel processing;

:Initialize empty **recordFutures** list\n(List<Future<SourceRecord>>);

|ParallelSmtBatchProcessor|
:Iterate records in order\n(**forEachOrdered** preserves submission order);

fork
    |Thread Pool (recordService)|
    :Submit **TransformRecord** callable\nto ExecutorService → **Future<SourceRecord>**;

    |ProcessingCallables.TransformRecord|
    :Execute **transformations.transform(record)**\nvia SMT Chain;

    if (transformedRecord != null?) then (yes — record passed SMTs)
        :Return **transformedRecord**\n(SourceRecord);
    else (no — filtered out by SMT)
        :Return **null**;
    endif

    |Thread Pool (recordService)|
    :Future<SourceRecord> ready;

fork again
    |Thread Pool (recordService)|
    :Submit **TransformRecord** callable\nto ExecutorService → **Future<SourceRecord>**;

    |ProcessingCallables.TransformRecord|
    :Execute **transformations.transform(record)**\nvia SMT Chain;

    if (transformedRecord != null?) then (yes — record passed SMTs)
        :Return **transformedRecord**\n(SourceRecord);
    else (no — filtered out by SMT)
        :Return **null**;
    endif

    |Thread Pool (recordService)|
    :Future<SourceRecord> ready;

end fork
note right
  All SourceRecords are submitted
  **in parallel** across thread pool workers.
  Submission order is preserved via
  forEachOrdered → futures collected
  in the same order.
end note

|ParallelSmtBatchProcessor|
:Collect all **Future<SourceRecord>**\ninto **recordFutures** list;

:Initialize empty **transformedRecords** list\n(List<SourceRecord>);

repeat
    :Call **future.get()**\n(blocking wait — no timeout);
    note right
      Blocks indefinitely
      until each worker thread
      completes its transform
    end note

    if (record != null?) then (yes — valid record)
        :Append record to\n**transformedRecords** list;
    else (no — null / SMT filtered)
        :Discard record silently\n(not added to batch);
    endif
repeat while (more futures?) is (yes)
-> no;

:Log TRACE — calling user handler;

|DebeziumEngine.ChangeConsumer (userHandler)|
:Call **userHandler.handleBatch**(\n    transformedRecords,\n    committer\n);
note right
  Offset commit responsibility
  belongs to the user-provided
  ChangeConsumer via committer
end note

|ParallelSmtBatchProcessor|
stop

@enduml
